    <description>Individually prescribed hospital based exercise in group two times a week, home-based exercise once a week. The exercise intervention consists of interval based aerobic exercise on a bicycle ergometer 30 minutes with intensity level at 13-17 at Borg scale, resistance exercises and balance exercises</description>
    <arm_group_label>Exercise</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Clinical diagnosis of acute coronary artery disease

          -  Aged 80 years or older

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Inability to understand or speak the Swedish language

          -  Serious physical or psychological disease interfering with participation in an
             exercise intervention

          -  Patients are already exercising three times or more/week
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>80 Years</minimum_age>
